The data presented were sampled between 1946 and 2012 from Windermere, a lake in northern England. The data were collected by the Freshwater Biological Association (FBA) and then by the Centre for Ecology and Hydrology and its predecessor Institute of Freshwater Ecology (IFE).  The files available in this series were used in Ohlberger et al.
